==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Your
<hw>Your</hw> <pr>(⟦umac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>pron. & a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>your</ets>, <ets>⟦yogh⟧our</ets>, <ets>eowr</ets>,
<ets>eower</ets>, AS. <ets>e⟦oacute⟧wer</ets>, originally used as the
gen. of <ets>ge</ets>, <ets>g⟦emac⟧</ets>, ye; akin to OFries.
<ets>iuwer</ets> your, OS. <ets>iuwar</ets>, D. <ets>uw</ets>, OHG.
<ets>iuw⟦emac⟧r</ets>, G. <ets>euer</ets>, Icel. <ets>y⟦edh⟧ar</ets>,
Goth. <ets>izwara</ets>, <ets>izwar</ets>, and E. <ets>you</ets>.
⟦root⟧189. See <er>You</er>.]</ety> <def>The form of the possessive case
of the personal pronoun <xex>you</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The possessive takes the form <xex>yours</xex> when the
noun to which it refers is not expressed, but implied; as, this book is
<xex>yours</xex>. ⟦ldquo⟧An old fellow of
<xex>yours</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</note> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yours</ent>⟦br⟧
